author: julianfoad
msg: In a #if, don't assume APU_HAVE_CRYPTO is defined, because in
older versions of ARP/APU it isn't.  (That wasn't strictly an error, but
my compiler gave a warning each time it processed this header.)
Remove "for ..." comments from #include directives, because such
comments always go out of date and aren't needed.
